category.name: book clubs
description:
Let's get together anywhere and everywhere to read and discuss books. Be it a cafe or a park, a crime or a classic novel, poetry, essays, be it just 3 people or 20.. let's share our passion for books, literature and a good read!

“There is only one way to read, which is to browse in libraries and bookshops, picking up books that attract you, reading only those, dropping them when they bore you, skipping the parts that drag-and never, never reading anything because you feel you ought, or because it is part of a trend or a movement. Remember that the book which bores you when you are twenty or thirty will open doors for you when you are forty or fifty-and vise versa. Don’t read a book out of its right time for you. ” 

― Doris Lessing
name: Book readers club
organizer.name: Angela

description:

category.name: book clubs
description: Ahlan:) My name is Ahmed, the audiobooks shaped the person I’m today. The first audiobook (you find the link below) was professionally produced by the Cultural center in Abu Dhabi (for around twenty years ago, recorded on kasett at that time). The audiobooks, in my private opinion, those now available on apps that anyone can download and listen to, is the greatest human invention after inventing the writing. This group is for those interested in this art that is growing fast with apps like Kitab Sawti, Iqraaly and other. Some of our meetup with by with Skype, so this group is open for people outside Stockholm. أهلا :) اسمي أحمد، الكتب الصوتية كونت الشخص الذي أنا هو اليوم. أول كتاب مسموع (تجد الرابط أدناه) تم إنتاجه من قبل المركز الثقافي في أبوظبي (منذ حوالي عشرين عاما، سجلت على كاسيت في ذلك الوقت). الكتب الصوتية, في رأيي الشخصي، المتوفرة الآن على التطبيقات الهاتف و التي يمكن لأي شخص تحميلها والاستماع لها، هو أعظم اختراع اوجدة الإنسان بعد اختراع الكتابة. هذه المجموعة هي للراغبين في هذا الفن الذي ينتشر بسرعة مع تطبيقات مثل كتاب صوتي، اقرالي وغيرها. كل لقاءاتنا ستكون مزودة بسكايب. الكروب يرحب بهوات الكتاب الصوتي في العالم وليس مرتبط بالساكنين في مكان معين.
name: Arabic audiobooks / الكتاب الصوتي المسموع

category.name: book clubs
description:
This book club will be one that spans psychological topics based on scientific research to the less scientific, but still thought-provoking self development books, including books focusing on behavioral change. And maybe some books leaning to the spiritual side, every once in a while!


I'd like to target every other month. I realize that the serious personal growth books may require more thought and discussion--if people are interested we can do a deeper dive.


I hope it goes without saying that we welcome a diverse group of backgrounds, races, and cultures to encourage interesting and engaging discussions.

category.name: book clubs
description:
Zwischen allen spannenden Aufgaben im neuen Land und dem ein oder anderen Moment voller Heimweh, vereint dieser Lesezirkel Stockholm alle Literaturliebhaber die sich auf Deutsch über deutschsprachige Bücher austauschen möchten und nebenbei ihre Muttersprache pflegen möchten. Die Autoren müssen nicht deutschsprachiger Herkunft sein, sondern können auch ins Deutsche übersetzte Schriften sein. 

<br>

Darüberhinaus unternimmt der German Book Club auch gemeinsame Unternehmungen zu Veranstaltungen des Goethe Instituts Stockholm oder anderen relevanten Veranstaltungen, die die Deutsche Kultur vermitteln. Besonders Literaturinterssierte und jene, die der schwedischen Sprache mächtig sind, werden hier auch gemeinsame Besuche zu Veranstaltungen aus dem skandinavischen Sprachraum unternehmen können.

<br>

Mein Hauptinteresse gilt Klassikern und Moderne aus Deutschland, Italien, Frankreich, Skandinavien und Südamerika sowie zeitgenössische diskutierte Romane und Feminismus aus Skandinavien.
name: German Book Club and more in Stockholm

category.name: book clubs
description:
We are a group of people who like to get together and discuss English language novels. The club (pronounced "Elba") includes people from Meetup, the Anglo-Swedish Society, and the British Club in Gothenburg. <br>

Our meetings are held in English in a museum apartment in Haga, Gothenburg. We meet at 18:30 on the third Tuesday of each month. We discuss the book for about an hour and then have a 'fika' and have a more free-ranging discussion for another hour. The cost of the meetup is 20 kronor each, to pay for the room and the fika. (We take cash or Swish.)

Each meeting has a discussion leader who gives a brief introduction to the book and gets the discussion going.
name: ELB(A) English Language Book Club
organizer.name: John

description:
Maybe you've fallen into a rut of bad habits that prevent you from reading as often as you'd like, but you've always had a long list of books you've wanted to read in your lifetime.

Or maybe you're an aspiring writer who needs some inspiration.

Let's choose a book to read and then talk about it. After a year you might have read 10, 20, maybe 30 good books, had some lively discussions, met some nice people and generally had a good time. Let's do it!

category.name: book clubs
description: Just like there are laws identified by our natural sciences regulating the material world, universal laws of the immaterial, immeasurable and undeniable spiritual world also exist. What is thought but a spiritual reality...and how do we think about what we want instead of what we don't want? According to Danish intuitive writer Martinus, thoughts are things on the spiritual plane, and by learning how to think eternal thoughts, we are training ourselves to live in eternal realities as opposed to living a limited physical existence. We read the books of Martinus and share our understanding of his world picture as it relates to our personal lives, well knowing it is a consideration or theoretical perspective we can choose to reject or internalize as part of our personal belief system.
name: Intuition Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
Det här är en grupp för kreativt skrivande som riktar sig till dig som gillar att prata om din egen och andras text.

Till varje möte skriver deltagarna en text utifrån ett tema som vi bestämt i förväg, för närvarande utgår vi från olika idiomatiska uttryck. Texterna delas en vecka innan mötet med dem som anmält sig till träffen. Alla läser allas texter och vid mötet pratar vi om varje text utifrån aspekter som stil, språk, målgrupp, betydelse och annat som skribenten önskar få feedback på

Vi lägger tyngdpunkten på det skönlitterära skrivandet. Texterna bör inte vara mer än en A4-sida lång för att vi ska ha tid att prata om alla.

Du som vill vara med i gruppen ska vara beredd på att skriva egna texter, dela dem med de andra i gruppen och både kunna och vilja ge och ta emot tankar kring din egen och andras text.

God, konstruktiv återkoppling är en självklarhet!

Vi träffas oftast på ett café i centrala Jönköping och fikar medan vi pratar.

Nyfiken på att vara med? Skicka en kort presentation av dig själv och ditt skrivande och välkommen att prova detta sätt att jobba med ett tydligt fokus och en deadline, och få en skrivarintresserad grupps stöd i ditt skapande.

<br>

<br>
name: Meetup för skrivare

category.name: book clubs
description:
We are a group of people who like to get together and discuss English language novels. The club (pronounced "Elba") includes people from Meetup, the Anglo-Swedish Society, and the British Club in Gothenburg. <br>

Our meetings are held in English in a museum apartment in Haga, Gothenburg. We meet at 18:30 on the third Tuesday of each month. We discuss the book for about an hour and then have a 'fika' and have a more free-ranging discussion for another hour. The cost of the meetup is 20 kronor each, to pay for the room and the fika. (We take cash or Swish.)

Each meeting has a discussion leader who gives a brief introduction to the book and gets the discussion going.
name: ELB(A) English Language Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
Let's get together anywhere and everywhere to read and discuss books. Be it a cafe or a park, a crime or a classic novel, poetry, essays, be it just 3 people or 20.. let's share our passion for books, literature and a good read!

“There is only one way to read, which is to browse in libraries and bookshops, picking up books that attract you, reading only those, dropping them when they bore you, skipping the parts that drag-and never, never reading anything because you feel you ought, or because it is part of a trend or a movement. Remember that the book which bores you when you are twenty or thirty will open doors for you when you are forty or fifty-and vise versa. Don’t read a book out of its right time for you. ” 

― Doris Lessing

category.name: book clubs
description: Ahlan:) My name is Ahmed, the audiobooks shaped the person I’m today. The first audiobook (you find the link below) was professionally produced by the Cultural center in Abu Dhabi (for around twenty years ago, recorded on kasett at that time). The audiobooks, in my private opinion, those now available on apps that anyone can download and listen to, is the greatest human invention after inventing the writing. This group is for those interested in this art that is growing fast with apps like Kitab Sawti, Iqraaly and other. Some of our meetup with by with Skype, so this group is open for people outside Stockholm. أهلا :) اسمي أحمد، الكتب الصوتية كونت الشخص الذي أنا هو اليوم. أول كتاب مسموع (تجد الرابط أدناه) تم إنتاجه من قبل المركز الثقافي في أبوظبي (منذ حوالي عشرين عاما، سجلت على كاسيت في ذلك الوقت). الكتب الصوتية, في رأيي الشخصي، المتوفرة الآن على التطبيقات الهاتف و التي يمكن لأي شخص تحميلها والاستماع لها، هو أعظم اختراع اوجدة الإنسان بعد اختراع الكتابة. هذه المجموعة هي للراغبين في هذا الفن الذي ينتشر بسرعة مع تطبيقات مثل كتاب صوتي، اقرالي وغيرها. كل لقاءاتنا ستكون مزودة بسكايب. الكروب يرحب بهوات الكتاب الصوتي في العالم وليس مرتبط بالساكنين في مكان معين.
name: Arabic audiobooks / الكتاب الصوتي المسموع

description:
This book club will be one that spans psychological topics based on scientific research to the less scientific, but still thought-provoking self development books, including books focusing on behavioral change. And maybe some books leaning to the spiritual side, every once in a while!


I'd like to target every other month. I realize that the serious personal growth books may require more thought and discussion--if people are interested we can do a deeper dive.


I hope it goes without saying that we welcome a diverse group of backgrounds, races, and cultures to encourage interesting and engaging discussions.

category.name: book clubs
description:
Zwischen allen spannenden Aufgaben im neuen Land und dem ein oder anderen Moment voller Heimweh, vereint dieser Lesezirkel Stockholm alle Literaturliebhaber die sich auf Deutsch über deutschsprachige Bücher austauschen möchten und nebenbei ihre Muttersprache pflegen möchten. Die Autoren müssen nicht deutschsprachiger Herkunft sein, sondern können auch ins Deutsche übersetzte Schriften sein. 

<br>

Darüberhinaus unternimmt der German Book Club auch gemeinsame Unternehmungen zu Veranstaltungen des Goethe Instituts Stockholm oder anderen relevanten Veranstaltungen, die die Deutsche Kultur vermitteln. Besonders Literaturinterssierte und jene, die der schwedischen Sprache mächtig sind, werden hier auch gemeinsame Besuche zu Veranstaltungen aus dem skandinavischen Sprachraum unternehmen können.

<br>

Mein Hauptinteresse gilt Klassikern und Moderne aus Deutschland, Italien, Frankreich, Skandinavien und Südamerika sowie zeitgenössische diskutierte Romane und Feminismus aus Skandinavien.
name: German Book Club and more in Stockholm

category.name: book clubs
description: Ahlan:) My name is Ahmed, the audiobooks shaped the person I’m today. The first audiobook (you find the link below) was professionally produced by the Cultural center in Abu Dhabi (for around twenty years ago, recorded on kasett at that time). The audiobooks, in my private opinion, those now available on apps that anyone can download and listen to, is the greatest human invention after inventing the writing. This group is for those interested in this art that is growing fast with apps like Kitab Sawti, Iqraaly and other. Some of our meetup with by with Skype, so this group is open for people outside Stockholm. أهلا :) اسمي أحمد، الكتب الصوتية كونت الشخص الذي أنا هو اليوم. أول كتاب مسموع (تجد الرابط أدناه) تم إنتاجه من قبل المركز الثقافي في أبوظبي (منذ حوالي عشرين عاما، سجلت على كاسيت في ذلك الوقت). الكتب الصوتية, في رأيي الشخصي، المتوفرة الآن على التطبيقات الهاتف و التي يمكن لأي شخص تحميلها والاستماع لها، هو أعظم اختراع اوجدة الإنسان بعد اختراع الكتابة. هذه المجموعة هي للراغبين في هذا الفن الذي ينتشر بسرعة مع تطبيقات مثل كتاب صوتي، اقرالي وغيرها. كل لقاءاتنا ستكون مزودة بسكايب. الكروب يرحب بهوات الكتاب الصوتي في العالم وليس مرتبط بالساكنين في مكان معين.
name: Arabic audiobooks / الكتاب الصوتي المسموع

category.name: book clubs
description:
This book club will be one that spans psychological topics based on scientific research to the less scientific, but still thought-provoking self development books, including books focusing on behavioral change. And maybe some books leaning to the spiritual side, every once in a while!


I'd like to target every other month. I realize that the serious personal growth books may require more thought and discussion--if people are interested we can do a deeper dive.


I hope it goes without saying that we welcome a diverse group of backgrounds, races, and cultures to encourage interesting and engaging discussions.
name: Reading for self development

category.name: book clubs
description:
Zwischen allen spannenden Aufgaben im neuen Land und dem ein oder anderen Moment voller Heimweh, vereint dieser Lesezirkel Stockholm alle Literaturliebhaber die sich auf Deutsch über deutschsprachige Bücher austauschen möchten und nebenbei ihre Muttersprache pflegen möchten. Die Autoren müssen nicht deutschsprachiger Herkunft sein, sondern können auch ins Deutsche übersetzte Schriften sein. 

<br>

Darüberhinaus unternimmt der German Book Club auch gemeinsame Unternehmungen zu Veranstaltungen des Goethe Instituts Stockholm oder anderen relevanten Veranstaltungen, die die Deutsche Kultur vermitteln. Besonders Literaturinterssierte und jene, die der schwedischen Sprache mächtig sind, werden hier auch gemeinsame Besuche zu Veranstaltungen aus dem skandinavischen Sprachraum unternehmen können.

<br>

Mein Hauptinteresse gilt Klassikern und Moderne aus Deutschland, Italien, Frankreich, Skandinavien und Südamerika sowie zeitgenössische diskutierte Romane und Feminismus aus Skandinavien.
name: German Book Club and more in Stockholm

category.name: book clubs
description:
Let's get together anywhere and everywhere to read and discuss books. Be it a cafe or a park, a crime or a classic novel, poetry, essays, be it just 3 people or 20.. let's share our passion for books, literature and a good read!

“There is only one way to read, which is to browse in libraries and bookshops, picking up books that attract you, reading only those, dropping them when they bore you, skipping the parts that drag-and never, never reading anything because you feel you ought, or because it is part of a trend or a movement. Remember that the book which bores you when you are twenty or thirty will open doors for you when you are forty or fifty-and vise versa. Don’t read a book out of its right time for you. ” 

― Doris Lessing
name: Book readers club
organizer.name: Angela

description: It doesn't matter if you're a dwarf, troll, undead, feegle or human, you will be welcome here! category.name: book clubs
description:
Are you also one of the people who leaves the book store or the libary with two or three books at the same time? Then this group is for you - the book lovers in Uppsala!
Let's get together to discuss books - let it be crime, fantasy, science fiction, historic novels or contemporary literature. Join me in a cafe or a picnic and share your passion and thoughts. At the end of each meeting we will decide about a new book to read and the aim is to choose a book from different genre.
I am looking forward to meet other book enthusiasts! :)
name: Uppsala Book Readers Meetup

category.name: book clubs
description:
Let's get together anywhere and everywhere to read and discuss books. Be it a cafe or a park, a crime or a classic novel, poetry, essays, be it just 3 people or 20.. let's share our passion for books, literature and a good read!

“There is only one way to read, which is to browse in libraries and bookshops, picking up books that attract you, reading only those, dropping them when they bore you, skipping the parts that drag-and never, never reading anything because you feel you ought, or because it is part of a trend or a movement. Remember that the book which bores you when you are twenty or thirty will open doors for you when you are forty or fifty-and vise versa. Don’t read a book out of its right time for you. ” 

― Doris Lessing
name: Book readers club

category.name: book clubs
description: Ahlan:) My name is Ahmed, the audiobooks shaped the person I’m today. The first audiobook (you find the link below) was professionally produced by the Cultural center in Abu Dhabi (for around twenty years ago, recorded on kasett at that time). The audiobooks, in my private opinion, those now available on apps that anyone can download and listen to, is the greatest human invention after inventing the writing. This group is for those interested in this art that is growing fast with apps like Kitab Sawti, Iqraaly and other. Some of our meetup with by with Skype, so this group is open for people outside Stockholm. أهلا :) اسمي أحمد، الكتب الصوتية كونت الشخص الذي أنا هو اليوم. أول كتاب مسموع (تجد الرابط أدناه) تم إنتاجه من قبل المركز الثقافي في أبوظبي (منذ حوالي عشرين عاما، سجلت على كاسيت في ذلك الوقت). الكتب الصوتية, في رأيي الشخصي، المتوفرة الآن على التطبيقات الهاتف و التي يمكن لأي شخص تحميلها والاستماع لها، هو أعظم اختراع اوجدة الإنسان بعد اختراع الكتابة. هذه المجموعة هي للراغبين في هذا الفن الذي ينتشر بسرعة مع تطبيقات مثل كتاب صوتي، اقرالي وغيرها. كل لقاءاتنا ستكون مزودة بسكايب. الكروب يرحب بهوات الكتاب الصوتي في العالم وليس مرتبط بالساكنين في مكان معين.
name: Arabic audiobooks / الكتاب الصوتي المسموع

description:
This book club will be one that spans psychological topics based on scientific research to the less scientific, but still thought-provoking self development books, including books focusing on behavioral change. And maybe some books leaning to the spiritual side, every once in a while!


I'd like to target every other month. I realize that the serious personal growth books may require more thought and discussion--if people are interested we can do a deeper dive.


I hope it goes without saying that we welcome a diverse group of backgrounds, races, and cultures to encourage interesting and engaging discussions.

category.name: book clubs
description:
Zwischen allen spannenden Aufgaben im neuen Land und dem ein oder anderen Moment voller Heimweh, vereint dieser Lesezirkel Stockholm alle Literaturliebhaber die sich auf Deutsch über deutschsprachige Bücher austauschen möchten und nebenbei ihre Muttersprache pflegen möchten. Die Autoren müssen nicht deutschsprachiger Herkunft sein, sondern können auch ins Deutsche übersetzte Schriften sein. 

<br>

Darüberhinaus unternimmt der German Book Club auch gemeinsame Unternehmungen zu Veranstaltungen des Goethe Instituts Stockholm oder anderen relevanten Veranstaltungen, die die Deutsche Kultur vermitteln. Besonders Literaturinterssierte und jene, die der schwedischen Sprache mächtig sind, werden hier auch gemeinsame Besuche zu Veranstaltungen aus dem skandinavischen Sprachraum unternehmen können.

<br>

Mein Hauptinteresse gilt Klassikern und Moderne aus Deutschland, Italien, Frankreich, Skandinavien und Südamerika sowie zeitgenössische diskutierte Romane und Feminismus aus Skandinavien.
name: German Book Club and more in Stockholm

category.name: book clubs
description:
Maybe you've fallen into a rut of bad habits that prevent you from reading as often as you'd like, but you've always had a long list of books you've wanted to read in your lifetime.

Or maybe you're an aspiring writer who needs some inspiration.

Let's choose a book to read and then talk about it. After a year you might have read 10, 20, maybe 30 good books, had some lively discussions, met some nice people and generally had a good time. Let's do it!

description: Just like there are laws identified by our natural sciences regulating the material world, universal laws of the immaterial, immeasurable and undeniable spiritual world also exist. What is thought but a spiritual reality...and how do we think about what we want instead of what we don't want? According to Danish intuitive writer Martinus, thoughts are things on the spiritual plane, and by learning how to think eternal thoughts, we are training ourselves to live in eternal realities as opposed to living a limited physical existence. We read the books of Martinus and share our understanding of his world picture as it relates to our personal lives, well knowing it is a consideration or theoretical perspective we can choose to reject or internalize as part of our personal belief system.
name: Intuition Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
We are a group of people who like to get together and discuss English language novels. The club (pronounced "Elba") includes people from Meetup, the Anglo-Swedish Society, and the British Club in Gothenburg. <br>

Our meetings are held in English in a museum apartment in Haga, Gothenburg. We meet at 18:30 on the third Tuesday of each month. We discuss the book for about an hour and then have a 'fika' and have a more free-ranging discussion for another hour. The cost of the meetup is 20 kronor each, to pay for the room and the fika. (We take cash or Swish.)

Each meeting has a discussion leader who gives a brief introduction to the book and gets the discussion going.
name: ELB(A) English Language Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description: Ahlan:) My name is Ahmed, the audiobooks shaped the person I’m today. The first audiobook (you find the link below) was professionally produced by the Cultural center in Abu Dhabi (for around twenty years ago, recorded on kasett at that time). The audiobooks, in my private opinion, those now available on apps that anyone can download and listen to, is the greatest human invention after inventing the writing. This group is for those interested in this art that is growing fast with apps like Kitab Sawti, Iqraaly and other. Some of our meetup with by with Skype, so this group is open for people outside Stockholm. أهلا :) اسمي أحمد، الكتب الصوتية كونت الشخص الذي أنا هو اليوم. أول كتاب مسموع (تجد الرابط أدناه) تم إنتاجه من قبل المركز الثقافي في أبوظبي (منذ حوالي عشرين عاما، سجلت على كاسيت في ذلك الوقت). الكتب الصوتية, في رأيي الشخصي، المتوفرة الآن على التطبيقات الهاتف و التي يمكن لأي شخص تحميلها والاستماع لها، هو أعظم اختراع اوجدة الإنسان بعد اختراع الكتابة. هذه المجموعة هي للراغبين في هذا الفن الذي ينتشر بسرعة مع تطبيقات مثل كتاب صوتي، اقرالي وغيرها. كل لقاءاتنا ستكون مزودة بسكايب. الكروب يرحب بهوات الكتاب الصوتي في العالم وليس مرتبط بالساكنين في مكان معين.
name: Arabic audiobooks / الكتاب الصوتي المسموع

description:
This book club will be one that spans psychological topics based on scientific research to the less scientific, but still thought-provoking self development books, including books focusing on behavioral change. And maybe some books leaning to the spiritual side, every once in a while!


I'd like to target every other month. I realize that the serious personal growth books may require more thought and discussion--if people are interested we can do a deeper dive.


I hope it goes without saying that we welcome a diverse group of backgrounds, races, and cultures to encourage interesting and engaging discussions.

category.name: book clubs
description:
Zwischen allen spannenden Aufgaben im neuen Land und dem ein oder anderen Moment voller Heimweh, vereint dieser Lesezirkel Stockholm alle Literaturliebhaber die sich auf Deutsch über deutschsprachige Bücher austauschen möchten und nebenbei ihre Muttersprache pflegen möchten. Die Autoren müssen nicht deutschsprachiger Herkunft sein, sondern können auch ins Deutsche übersetzte Schriften sein. 

<br>

Darüberhinaus unternimmt der German Book Club auch gemeinsame Unternehmungen zu Veranstaltungen des Goethe Instituts Stockholm oder anderen relevanten Veranstaltungen, die die Deutsche Kultur vermitteln. Besonders Literaturinterssierte und jene, die der schwedischen Sprache mächtig sind, werden hier auch gemeinsame Besuche zu Veranstaltungen aus dem skandinavischen Sprachraum unternehmen können.

<br>

Mein Hauptinteresse gilt Klassikern und Moderne aus Deutschland, Italien, Frankreich, Skandinavien und Südamerika sowie zeitgenössische diskutierte Romane und Feminismus aus Skandinavien.
name: German Book Club and more in Stockholm

description:

Or maybe you're an aspiring writer who needs some inspiration.

Let's choose a book to read and then talk about it. After a year you might have read 10, 20, maybe 30 good books, had some lively discussions, met some nice people and generally had a good time. Let's do it!

description: Just like there are laws identified by our natural sciences regulating the material world, universal laws of the immaterial, immeasurable and undeniable spiritual world also exist. What is thought but a spiritual reality...and how do we think about what we want instead of what we don't want? According to Danish intuitive writer Martinus, thoughts are things on the spiritual plane, and by learning how to think eternal thoughts, we are training ourselves to live in eternal realities as opposed to living a limited physical existence. We read the books of Martinus and share our understanding of his world picture as it relates to our personal lives, well knowing it is a consideration or theoretical perspective we can choose to reject or internalize as part of our personal belief system.
name: Intuition Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
We are a group of people who like to get together and discuss English language novels. The club (pronounced "Elba") includes people from Meetup, the Anglo-Swedish Society, and the British Club in Gothenburg. <br>

Our meetings are held in English in a museum apartment in Haga, Gothenburg. We meet at 18:30 on the third Tuesday of each month. We discuss the book for about an hour and then have a 'fika' and have a more free-ranging discussion for another hour. The cost of the meetup is 20 kronor each, to pay for the room and the fika. (We take cash or Swish.)

Each meeting has a discussion leader who gives a brief introduction to the book and gets the discussion going.
name: ELB(A) English Language Book Club

category.name: book clubs
description:
Let's get together anywhere and everywhere to read and discuss books. Be it a cafe or a park, a crime or a classic novel, poetry, essays, be it just 3 people or 20.. let's share our passion for books, literature and a good read!

“There is only one way to read, which is to browse in libraries and bookshops, picking up books that attract you, reading only those, dropping them when they bore you, skipping the parts that drag-and never, never reading anything because you feel you ought, or because it is part of a trend or a movement. Remember that the book which bores you when you are twenty or thirty will open doors for you when you are forty or fifty-and vise versa. Don’t read a book out of its right time for you. ” 

― Doris Lessing
name: Book readers club
organizer.name: Angela

category.name: book clubs
description:
Are you also one of the people who leaves the book store or the libary with two or three books at the same time? Then this group is for you - the book lovers in Uppsala!
Let's get together to discuss books - let it be crime, fantasy, science fiction, historic novels or contemporary literature. Join me in a cafe or a picnic and share your passion and thoughts. At the end of each meeting we will decide about a new book to read and the aim is to choose a book from different genre.
I am looking forward to meet other book enthusiasts! :)
name: Uppsala Book Readers Meetup

category.name: book clubs
description: Ahlan:) My name is Ahmed, the audiobooks shaped the person I’m today. The first audiobook (you find the link below) was professionally produced by the Cultural center in Abu Dhabi (for around twenty years ago, recorded on kasett at that time). The audiobooks, in my private opinion, those now available on apps that anyone can download and listen to, is the greatest human invention after inventing the writing. This group is for those interested in this art that is growing fast with apps like Kitab Sawti, Iqraaly and other. Some of our meetup with by with Skype, so this group is open for people outside Stockholm. أهلا :) اسمي أحمد، الكتب الصوتية كونت الشخص الذي أنا هو اليوم. أول كتاب مسموع (تجد الرابط أدناه) تم إنتاجه من قبل المركز الثقافي في أبوظبي (منذ حوالي عشرين عاما، سجلت على كاسيت في ذلك الوقت). الكتب الصوتية, في رأيي الشخصي، المتوفرة الآن على التطبيقات الهاتف و التي يمكن لأي شخص تحميلها والاستماع لها، هو أعظم اختراع اوجدة الإنسان بعد اختراع الكتابة. هذه المجموعة هي للراغبين في هذا الفن الذي ينتشر بسرعة مع تطبيقات مثل كتاب صوتي، اقرالي وغيرها. كل لقاءاتنا ستكون مزودة بسكايب. الكروب يرحب بهوات الكتاب الصوتي في العالم وليس مرتبط بالساكنين في مكان معين.
name: Arabic audiobooks / الكتاب الصوتي المسموع

category.name: book clubs
description:
This book club will be one that spans psychological topics based on scientific research to the less scientific, but still thought-provoking self development books, including books focusing on behavioral change. And maybe some books leaning to the spiritual side, every once in a while!


I'd like to target every other month. I realize that the serious personal growth books may require more thought and discussion--if people are interested we can do a deeper dive.


I hope it goes without saying that we welcome a diverse group of backgrounds, races, and cultures to encourage interesting and engaging discussions.
name: Reading for self development

category.name: book clubs
description:
Zwischen allen spannenden Aufgaben im neuen Land und dem ein oder anderen Moment voller Heimweh, vereint dieser Lesezirkel Stockholm alle Literaturliebhaber die sich auf Deutsch über deutschsprachige Bücher austauschen möchten und nebenbei ihre Muttersprache pflegen möchten. Die Autoren müssen nicht deutschsprachiger Herkunft sein, sondern können auch ins Deutsche übersetzte Schriften sein. 

<br>

Darüberhinaus unternimmt der German Book Club auch gemeinsame Unternehmungen zu Veranstaltungen des Goethe Instituts Stockholm oder anderen relevanten Veranstaltungen, die die Deutsche Kultur vermitteln. Besonders Literaturinterssierte und jene, die der schwedischen Sprache mächtig sind, werden hier auch gemeinsame Besuche zu Veranstaltungen aus dem skandinavischen Sprachraum unternehmen können.

<br>

Mein Hauptinteresse gilt Klassikern und Moderne aus Deutschland, Italien, Frankreich, Skandinavien und Südamerika sowie zeitgenössische diskutierte Romane und Feminismus aus Skandinavien.
name: German Book Club and more in Stockholm

category.name: book clubs
description:
Let's get together anywhere and everywhere to read and discuss books. Be it a cafe or a park, a crime or a classic novel, poetry, essays, be it just 3 people or 20.. let's share our passion for books, literature and a good read!

“There is only one way to read, which is to browse in libraries and bookshops, picking up books that attract you, reading only those, dropping them when they bore you, skipping the parts that drag-and never, never reading anything because you feel you ought, or because it is part of a trend or a movement. Remember that the book which bores you when you are twenty or thirty will open doors for you when you are forty or fifty-and vise versa. Don’t read a book out of its right time for you. ” 

― Doris Lessing
name: Book readers club

description:
Välkommen till en bokcirkel där samtalen kring de böcker vi läser är på svenska.

Vi väljer alltid bok till nästa mötet i samband med bokträffen, så missa inte chansen att vara med och påverka vad vi ska läsa. Bokträffarna äger alltid rum i centrala Stockholm.

Kom och diskutera böcker med oss!

category.name: book clubs
description:
Are you also one of the people who leaves the book store or the libary with two or three books at the same time? Then this group is for you - the book lovers in Uppsala!
Let's get together to discuss books - let it be crime, fantasy, science fiction, historic novels or contemporary literature. Join me in a cafe or a picnic and share your passion and thoughts. At the end of each meeting we will decide about a new book to read and the aim is to choose a book from different genre.
I am looking forward to meet other book enthusiasts! :)
name: Uppsala Book Readers Meetup

category.name: book clubs
description: Ahlan:) My name is Ahmed, the audiobooks shaped the person I’m today. The first audiobook (you find the link below) was professionally produced by the Cultural center in Abu Dhabi (for around twenty years ago, recorded on kasett at that time). The audiobooks, in my private opinion, those now available on apps that anyone can download and listen to, is the greatest human invention after inventing the writing. This group is for those interested in this art that is growing fast with apps like Kitab Sawti, Iqraaly and other. Some of our meetup with by with Skype, so this group is open for people outside Stockholm. أهلا :) اسمي أحمد، الكتب الصوتية كونت الشخص الذي أنا هو اليوم. أول كتاب مسموع (تجد الرابط أدناه) تم إنتاجه من قبل المركز الثقافي في أبوظبي (منذ حوالي عشرين عاما، سجلت على كاسيت في ذلك الوقت). الكتب الصوتية, في رأيي الشخصي، المتوفرة الآن على التطبيقات الهاتف و التي يمكن لأي شخص تحميلها والاستماع لها، هو أعظم اختراع اوجدة الإنسان بعد اختراع الكتابة. هذه المجموعة هي للراغبين في هذا الفن الذي ينتشر بسرعة مع تطبيقات مثل كتاب صوتي، اقرالي وغيرها. كل لقاءاتنا ستكون مزودة بسكايب. الكروب يرحب بهوات الكتاب الصوتي في العالم وليس مرتبط بالساكنين في مكان معين.
name: Arabic audiobooks / الكتاب الصوتي المسموع

category.name: book clubs
description:
This book club will be one that spans psychological topics based on scientific research to the less scientific, but still thought-provoking self development books, including books focusing on behavioral change. And maybe some books leaning to the spiritual side, every once in a while!


I'd like to target every other month. I realize that the serious personal growth books may require more thought and discussion--if people are interested we can do a deeper dive.


I hope it goes without saying that we welcome a diverse group of backgrounds, races, and cultures to encourage interesting and engaging discussions.
name: Reading for self development

category.name: book clubs
description:
Zwischen allen spannenden Aufgaben im neuen Land und dem ein oder anderen Moment voller Heimweh, vereint dieser Lesezirkel Stockholm alle Literaturliebhaber die sich auf Deutsch über deutschsprachige Bücher austauschen möchten und nebenbei ihre Muttersprache pflegen möchten. Die Autoren müssen nicht deutschsprachiger Herkunft sein, sondern können auch ins Deutsche übersetzte Schriften sein. 

<br>

Darüberhinaus unternimmt der German Book Club auch gemeinsame Unternehmungen zu Veranstaltungen des Goethe Instituts Stockholm oder anderen relevanten Veranstaltungen, die die Deutsche Kultur vermitteln. Besonders Literaturinterssierte und jene, die der schwedischen Sprache mächtig sind, werden hier auch gemeinsame Besuche zu Veranstaltungen aus dem skandinavischen Sprachraum unternehmen können.

<br>

Mein Hauptinteresse gilt Klassikern und Moderne aus Deutschland, Italien, Frankreich, Skandinavien und Südamerika sowie zeitgenössische diskutierte Romane und Feminismus aus Skandinavien.
name: German Book Club and more in Stockholm

category.name: book clubs
description:
Let's get together anywhere and everywhere to read and discuss books. Be it a cafe or a park, a crime or a classic novel, poetry, essays, be it just 3 people or 20.. let's share our passion for books, literature and a good read!

“There is only one way to read, which is to browse in libraries and bookshops, picking up books that attract you, reading only those, dropping them when they bore you, skipping the parts that drag-and never, never reading anything because you feel you ought, or because it is part of a trend or a movement. Remember that the book which bores you when you are twenty or thirty will open doors for you when you are forty or fifty-and vise versa. Don’t read a book out of its right time for you. ” 

― Doris Lessing
name: Book readers club

description: It doesn't matter if you're a dwarf, troll, undead, feegle or human, you will be welcome here! description:
إذا كُنتم من عشاق الأدب العربيّ وتودون تعزيز هذه الهواية فأهلاً بكم في: نادي الكتاب العربيّ

الفكرة والغرض الأساسي من هذا النادي هو تحفيز قرائتنا الأدبيّة العربيّة وزيادة مُعدل هذه القراءات. في كل ثلاثة أسابيع/شهر سنقوم بأختيار كتاب محدد للقرآءة، ثم نلتقي لغرض مناقشة وتحليل هذا الكتاب. وبالطبع سيكون من دواعي سرورنا استقبال اقتراحتكم بشأن الأعمال الأدبيّة التي تودون أن نقرأها معاً في النادي مُستقبلاً، فأهلاً بكم!

category.name: book clubs
description:
I am a native English speaker living in Sweden and wanting to start a Book Club for women. You are:
• A person who enjoys reading and is able to read in English well.
• Want to improve your English through discussion around literature.
• Interested in different cultures.
• Intellectually curious and imaginative.
• Interested and enjoy the company of others.

If this appeals to you, please contact me: dawne-g-zetterstrom@live.co.uk and we can discuss details. I look forward to hearing from you.

category.name: book clubs
description:
Let's get together anywhere and everywhere to read and discuss books. Be it a cafe or a park, a crime or a classic novel, poetry, essays, be it just 3 people or 20.. let's share our passion for books, literature and a good read!

“There is only one way to read, which is to browse in libraries and bookshops, picking up books that attract you, reading only those, dropping them when they bore you, skipping the parts that drag-and never, never reading anything because you feel you ought, or because it is part of a trend or a movement. Remember that the book which bores you when you are twenty or thirty will open doors for you when you are forty or fifty-and vise versa. Don’t read a book out of its right time for you. ” 

― Doris Lessing
name: Book readers club
organizer.name: Angela

description:
Are you also one of the people who leaves the book store or the libary with two or three books at the same time? Then this group is for you - the book lovers in Uppsala!
Let's get together to discuss books - let it be crime, fantasy, science fiction, historic novels or contemporary literature. Join me in a cafe or a picnic and share your passion and thoughts. At the end of each meeting we will decide about a new book to read and the aim is to choose a book from different genre.
I am looking forward to meet other book enthusiasts! :)

category.name: book clubs
description: Ahlan:) My name is Ahmed, the audiobooks shaped the person I’m today. The first audiobook (you find the link below) was professionally produced by the Cultural center in Abu Dhabi (for around twenty years ago, recorded on kasett at that time). The audiobooks, in my private opinion, those now available on apps that anyone can download and listen to, is the greatest human invention after inventing the writing. This group is for those interested in this art that is growing fast with apps like Kitab Sawti, Iqraaly and other. Some of our meetup with by with Skype, so this group is open for people outside Stockholm. أهلا :) اسمي أحمد، الكتب الصوتية كونت الشخص الذي أنا هو اليوم. أول كتاب مسموع (تجد الرابط أدناه) تم إنتاجه من قبل المركز الثقافي في أبوظبي (منذ حوالي عشرين عاما، سجلت على كاسيت في ذلك الوقت). الكتب الصوتية, في رأيي الشخصي، المتوفرة الآن على التطبيقات الهاتف و التي يمكن لأي شخص تحميلها والاستماع لها، هو أعظم اختراع اوجدة الإنسان بعد اختراع الكتابة. هذه المجموعة هي للراغبين في هذا الفن الذي ينتشر بسرعة مع تطبيقات مثل كتاب صوتي، اقرالي وغيرها. كل لقاءاتنا ستكون مزودة بسكايب. الكروب يرحب بهوات الكتاب الصوتي في العالم وليس مرتبط بالساكنين في مكان معين.
name: Arabic audiobooks / الكتاب الصوتي المسموع

category.name: book clubs
description:
This book club will be one that spans psychological topics based on scientific research to the less scientific, but still thought-provoking self development books, including books focusing on behavioral change. And maybe some books leaning to the spiritual side, every once in a while!


I'd like to target every other month. I realize that the serious personal growth books may require more thought and discussion--if people are interested we can do a deeper dive.


I hope it goes without saying that we welcome a diverse group of backgrounds, races, and cultures to encourage interesting and engaging discussions.

category.name: book clubs
description:
Zwischen allen spannenden Aufgaben im neuen Land und dem ein oder anderen Moment voller Heimweh, vereint dieser Lesezirkel Stockholm alle Literaturliebhaber die sich auf Deutsch über deutschsprachige Bücher austauschen möchten und nebenbei ihre Muttersprache pflegen möchten. Die Autoren müssen nicht deutschsprachiger Herkunft sein, sondern können auch ins Deutsche übersetzte Schriften sein. 

<br>

Darüberhinaus unternimmt der German Book Club auch gemeinsame Unternehmungen zu Veranstaltungen des Goethe Instituts Stockholm oder anderen relevanten Veranstaltungen, die die Deutsche Kultur vermitteln. Besonders Literaturinterssierte und jene, die der schwedischen Sprache mächtig sind, werden hier auch gemeinsame Besuche zu Veranstaltungen aus dem skandinavischen Sprachraum unternehmen können.

<br>

Mein Hauptinteresse gilt Klassikern und Moderne aus Deutschland, Italien, Frankreich, Skandinavien und Südamerika sowie zeitgenössische diskutierte Romane und Feminismus aus Skandinavien.
name: German Book Club and more in Stockholm

category.name: book clubs
description:
Det här är en grupp för kreativt skrivande som riktar sig till dig som gillar att prata om din egen och andras text.

Till varje möte skriver deltagarna en text utifrån ett tema som vi bestämt i förväg, för närvarande utgår vi från olika idiomatiska uttryck. Texterna delas en vecka innan mötet med dem som anmält sig till träffen. Alla läser allas texter och vid mötet pratar vi om varje text utifrån aspekter som stil, språk, målgrupp, betydelse och annat som skribenten önskar få feedback på

Vi lägger tyngdpunkten på det skönlitterära skrivandet. Texterna bör inte vara mer än en A4-sida lång för att vi ska ha tid att prata om alla.

Du som vill vara med i gruppen ska vara beredd på att skriva egna texter, dela dem med de andra i gruppen och både kunna och vilja ge och ta emot tankar kring din egen och andras text.

God, konstruktiv återkoppling är en självklarhet!

Vi träffas oftast på ett café i centrala Jönköping och fikar medan vi pratar.

Nyfiken på att vara med? Skicka en kort presentation av dig själv och ditt skrivande och välkommen att prova detta sätt att jobba med ett tydligt fokus och en deadline, och få en skrivarintresserad grupps stöd i ditt skapande.

<br>

<br>
name: Meetup för skrivare

category.name: book clubs
description:
We are a group of people who like to get together and discuss English language novels. The club (pronounced "Elba") includes people from Meetup, the Anglo-Swedish Society, and the British Club in Gothenburg. <br>

Our meetings are held in English in a museum apartment in Haga, Gothenburg. We meet at 18:30 on the third Tuesday of each month. We discuss the book for about an hour and then have a 'fika' and have a more free-ranging discussion for another hour. The cost of the meetup is 20 kronor each, to pay for the room and the fika. (We take cash or Swish.)

Each meeting has a discussion leader who gives a brief introduction to the book and gets the discussion going.
name: ELB(A) English Language Book Club
organizer.name: John

category.name: book clubs
description:
Let's get together anywhere and everywhere to read and discuss books. Be it a cafe or a park, a crime or a classic novel, poetry, essays, be it just 3 people or 20.. let's share our passion for books, literature and a good read!

“There is only one way to read, which is to browse in libraries and bookshops, picking up books that attract you, reading only those, dropping them when they bore you, skipping the parts that drag-and never, never reading anything because you feel you ought, or because it is part of a trend or a movement. Remember that the book which bores you when you are twenty or thirty will open doors for you when you are forty or fifty-and vise versa. Don’t read a book out of its right time for you. ” 

― Doris Lessing
name: Book readers club

description:

Or maybe you're an aspiring writer who needs some inspiration.

Let's choose a book to read and then talk about it. After a year you might have read 10, 20, maybe 30 good books, had some lively discussions, met some nice people and generally had a good time. Let's do it!

description: Just like there are laws identified by our natural sciences regulating the material world, universal laws of the immaterial, immeasurable and undeniable spiritual world also exist. What is thought but a spiritual reality...and how do we think about what we want instead of what we don't want? According to Danish intuitive writer Martinus, thoughts are things on the spiritual plane, and by learning how to think eternal thoughts, we are training ourselves to live in eternal realities as opposed to living a limited physical existence. We read the books of Martinus and share our understanding of his world picture as it relates to our personal lives, well knowing it is a consideration or theoretical perspective we can choose to reject or internalize as part of our personal belief system.
